WEBVTT

00:02.562 --> 00:08.830
were astronomical, the projections that are 
embodied in the project agreement. In 1989, for

00:09.651 --> 00:20.185
example, the Woodlands would have built over 
4,000 dwelling units. We will do, in 1990, about

00:20.205 --> 00:31.320
950 dwelling units, less than a quarter of what was 
projected to have been done last year. In our best

00:31.520 --> 00:38.810
year, we did about 1,200 dwelling units, and that 
was in the heyday of Houston. The project

00:38.850 --> 00:48.703
agreement contemplated we would have sold that 
many units, sold or built for rent that many units

00:38.850 --> 00:48.703
the first year in development. So it's clearly 
over-optimistic

00:48.723 --> 00:55.873
if you want to give people the benefit of the doubt. 
And then, too, we've added more land to the

00:56.545 --> 00:59.108
woodlands. We've added 50 percent to the land mass 
of the woodlands. So even if we had hit those

01:01.651 --> 01:11.221
projections, we'd still be about a third below 
completion, or where we should be in 1992. So in

01:11.261 --> 01:19.430
1992, if the date hadn't been in there, transition 
will occur because the Covenant's saying that it

01:11.261 --> 01:19.430
will. And the Board will become 
resident-controlled.

01:24.693 --> 01:39.549
The Woodlands Corporation will lose control of a 
very important institution in the Woodlands,

01:24.693 --> 01:39.549
very important to the servicing of the Woodlands 
and the marketing of the Woodlands, long before

01:24.693 --> 01:39.549
the Woodlands is 85% complete. So we then had to 
say, well, what could we do?

01:46.036 --> 01:50.160
We could not afford to lose control of the 
Woodlands. or we could lose control of the WCA, but

01:51.727 --> 02:13.699
within the covenants, there's an entity that's 
created called the Development Standards

01:51.727 --> 02:13.699
Committee, and that is responsible for 
establishing design criteria, development

01:51.727 --> 02:13.699
standards, and approving all new construction 
that goes on in the Woodlands. And the covenants

02:14.039 --> 02:19.607
say that the Woodlands Corporation would have 
control of the DSC, through 1992 to August of 1992.

02:24.381 --> 02:31.251
And then after that, it becomes a function of the 
WCA, which in 1992 becomes resident control.

02:32.072 --> 02:38.841
That's like creating a planning commission or a 
zoning board controlled by the residents. And

02:38.862 --> 02:49.797
then they could, if we were to continue the 
Woodlands Covenants on new properties, we would

02:38.862 --> 02:49.797
have to go to them and say, can we build this product 
again? You know, and that's just not workable.

02:56.269 --> 03:11.865
So while we wished the 1992 date were not in the 
covenants and that we could continue as we are now

02:56.269 --> 03:11.865
because it's working very well, and many 
residents have said to us, I wish we could continue

02:56.269 --> 03:11.865
because we like the involvement of the Women's 
Corporation. We think it adds stability. We think

03:13.106 --> 03:16.169
it adds quality. We're going to honor the 
provisions of the covenants and transfer of

03:19.831 --> 03:23.356
control of the board in 1992.

03:26.061 --> 03:31.389
That leaves a large area of the Woodlands under the 
WCA. We will create two new associations for the

03:32.230 --> 03:44.809
new areas of development, the residential 
association and the commercial association,

03:32.230 --> 03:44.809
which we will control until 85% of development. 
And we're not going to put a date certain in those

03:44.829 --> 03:46.933
covenants. We're not going to make the same 
mistake. And so what we have is we honor

03:50.577 --> 03:56.002
transition. We set up new associations. And then 
we and the elected directors who now serve on the

03:59.626 --> 04:09.896
WCA board have put our heads together and say, is it 
best to have three associations operating

03:59.626 --> 04:09.896
independently? Or is it better in some way to 
create a working relationship where we can

04:17.442 --> 04:23.508
achieve economies of scale and efficiencies of 
management. And by doing that, we all can benefit.

04:28.293 --> 04:30.395
The obvious answer is yes, that would be best. How 
could we do it? And we have come up with the notion of

04:32.578 --> 04:42.067
a services corporation to which the WCA staff 
would be transferred. And it would be...

04:44.982 --> 04:57.515
corporation, a nonprofit corporation that 
administers the affairs of all three

04:44.982 --> 04:57.515
associations,

04:44.982 --> 04:57.515
responding to the wishes of the respective boards 
of each association. So it's not an umbrella

04:57.535 --> 05:00.097
association. It's a services corporation that 
works under contract with each of the

05:00.277 --> 05:10.308
associations and takes its marching orders from 
the boards of each of the associations. That is

05:11.228 --> 05:13.791
what we have been presenting to the community. It 
is a hard concept for people to understand because

05:14.193 --> 05:24.326
they have always thought that the woodlands would 
be served by one association. Frankly, I think all

05:25.547 --> 05:34.959
of us have gotten so used to the one association 
that it's even hard for us to even contemplate

05:25.547 --> 05:34.959
setting up other associations. And if there is any

05:42.273 --> 05:45.316
or hesitancy on the part of the community. It's, 
why are you changing things? It's working so well.

05:51.221 --> 06:03.673
Well, we're changing it because we, as a 
developer, have to know that we can be responsive

05:51.221 --> 06:03.673
to market conditions. It's almost like what I 
described with HUD. That was a very difficult

06:06.555 --> 06:11.520
partnership, and if we allowed the DSC which would 
be resident-controlled,

06:12.378 --> 06:39.783
to be the throttle for new development, then we're 
not really having the freedom to make adjustments

06:12.378 --> 06:39.783
to the master plan as they need to be to change the 
product when the market says, you know, years ago

06:12.378 --> 06:39.783
we could build townhouses in the woodlands and 
sell them. You couldn't sell a townhouse today. So

06:41.825 --> 06:46.731
we've had to adjust our program. We will get back 
into townhouse development, I'm sure, but for the

06:46.792 --> 06:51.778
time being, we'll have to wait. And during the 
recession, you could not build apartments and

06:51.798 --> 06:56.605
rent them. The vacancy rate in apartments was 
tremendous. Well, the residents, some of the

07:00.470 --> 07:07.579
residents who are control-motivated don't fully 
appreciate that. what a developer has to do to

07:07.728 --> 07:12.894
respond to market conditions and so forth. And 
then you would have people coming and going on that

07:13.474 --> 07:37.701
development standards committee, whereas by 
creating the new associations, we set up the

07:13.474 --> 07:37.701
development standards committees within them, 
which we would control and have the continuity of

07:13.474 --> 07:37.701
the developer representation, have the 
professionalism of architects and engineers and

07:13.474 --> 07:37.701
developer type people on that committee. We're 
setting up the other association, but trying to

07:38.170 --> 07:56.106
keep, through the Services Corporation, the 
notion which we all like, that is the unity of the

07:38.170 --> 07:56.106
woodlands, the cohesiveness of the woodlands, 
and... And the continuity of the... Continuity of

07:38.170 --> 07:56.106
services. There'd still be one number to call if 
you need some help or have a question, and so forth.

08:04.013 --> 08:05.815
The proposal is getting... very good reception. 
It's taking people a long time to understand why we

08:08.860 --> 08:15.586
have to do this. And it's taking them time to 
understand that generally when they do, they call

08:15.606 --> 08:29.640
us or see them out on the streets and so forth, and 
they say, you know, we finally understand what

08:15.606 --> 08:29.640
you're trying to do, and it makes a lot of sense. 
There are a handful of people, and literally I

08:30.261 --> 08:35.886
would say no more than a dozen people, who have 
expressed vocal opposition to it. And out of

08:39.607 --> 08:46.915
30,000 people, you could expect some... What's 
the basis of their opposition? They think the

08:46.935 --> 08:52.602
developer is trying to wrest control from the WCA. 
They don't understand that the WCA board, which

08:53.383 --> 09:01.091
will be resident control, will be the authority 
for the WCA. It's somehow in their minds. They see

09:03.558 --> 09:08.827
the services corporation as being the 
controlling entity. It is not. It works at the

09:09.568 --> 09:19.164
behest of the board of the WCA or the board of WCA2, 
which is what we're calling it for lack of a name

09:09.568 --> 09:19.164
right now. And they don't fully understand the 
relationship. If you were to do an organizational

09:23.051 --> 09:28.941
chart, you would have the WCA board up here, And 
then you would have the Services Corporation as a

09:29.444 --> 09:42.483
really dotted line relationship to the board, 
beneath the board. It's not superior to the board.

09:45.367 --> 09:48.812
And that's where they really don't understand 
that. And what is your role in this transition?

09:52.337 --> 09:54.520
Guiding it and making sure that it happens. Your 
chief flag waver? Well, I'm one of the authors. of

09:59.397 --> 10:00.858
the transition proposal. We had a committee of 
four who conceived it, then brought it to the board

10:01.719 --> 10:14.790
of the association, which

10:01.719 --> 10:14.790
endorsed it. And now we're presenting it to the 
public, and presumably... Who were the other

10:15.390 --> 10:20.655
four? Well, of the three, Scott Cummings, who's 
the general manager of the WCA, Eric Wojnar, who

10:29.890 --> 10:36.644
works for the Women's Corporation, at that time 
was controller and serves as the treasurer of the

10:29.890 --> 10:36.644
WCA. And Brian Reed, who was the attorney for the 
WCA. Four of us conceived of this notion.

10:45.567 --> 10:53.554
presented it to the board, and the people who 
really have to buy off on it are the four resident

10:45.567 --> 10:53.554
elected directors of the WCA. The WCA has four of 
11, seven of whom are appointed by the Women's

10:53.634 --> 11:00.681
Corporation, four of whom are elected by the 
community. So what it came to was those four had to

11:01.802 --> 11:14.173
agree to it, and there were some substantial 
negotiations between the elected directors and

11:01.802 --> 11:14.173
the Women's Corporation. Their biggest concern 
was if you stop the growth of the WCA, you freeze its

11:14.609 --> 11:28.302
tax base, much the way a city's tax base would be 
frozen if it could not annex. And they wanted to

11:29.222 --> 11:34.147
annex the rest of the property. And we explored 
that. But it wouldn't work because it would

11:35.949 --> 11:41.734
undermine the economic viability of the second 
association. So we said, well, how can we? let you,

11:43.735 --> 11:52.629
the WCA, benefit from that growth but not annex 
those properties. And what we came up with was a

11:52.649 --> 12:02.385
mechanism for sharing in certain costs of the WCA. 
by the other associations who implicitly built in

12:03.395 --> 12:08.041
a bit of a subsidy. So there is cash flowing from the 
other associations into the WCA to, in effect,

12:08.061 --> 12:15.351
subsidize. It was a little bit complicated. But 
that lowers the tax bite also. But it would lower

12:18.915 --> 12:21.959
the tax bite of this. From what you said, I gathered 
that the 1992 was a, I mean, there's no argument

12:23.121 --> 12:27.667
with that. That was in the covenants. It was a 
got-to-do. That's right. What other issues

