guiding principles, then? Those were the guiding

14:00.449 --> 14:02.431
principles. Have there been any basic tensions 
between the residents, say, and the population

14:02.451 --> 14:17.224
over the past years that are also involved, other 
than the expansion issue and the tax base, I guess,

14:02.451 --> 14:17.224
issue? There have been issues from time to time 
that have produced tension. In the early years,

14:27.524 --> 14:38.580
The Woodlands Corporation people, not knowing 
anything about community management, made a

14:27.524 --> 14:38.580
mistake that so many developers still make. And I 
lecture about this at the national conferences of

14:38.660 --> 14:50.317
community associations and to developers. When 
you take fiduciary responsibility of an

14:54.085 --> 15:17.477
association when you are the trustee of an 
association you have a responsibility to the

14:54.085 --> 15:17.477
residents like it or not that association is not 
your business it is a private nonprofit

14:54.085 --> 15:17.477
corporation that you for a time being have been 
entrusted to manage well And most developers

15:17.761 --> 15:22.446
don't realize that, particularly if they're 
doing it for the first time. In the early years, the

15:23.247 --> 15:29.754
Women's Corporation held the WCM meetings in 
somebody's office in this building. And the

15:29.774 --> 15:31.917
residents are saying, that's our association. We 
are members. The Covenant's established us as

15:32.698 --> 15:35.120
members of the association. We don't know what's 
going on. Well, that got the Women's Corporation

15:37.503 --> 15:42.408
and the residents off on the wrong foot. I mean, it 
really did in that last years. suspicion

15:47.073 --> 15:57.848
developed that,

15:47.073 --> 15:57.848
well, a distrust between the company and the 
residents. So they started holding public

15:58.349 --> 16:01.192
meetings. But the manner in which those meetings 
were held only inflamed those suspicions.

16:12.233 --> 16:22.749
The president and the board tended to like to call 
the majority he had on the board on all votes. So it

16:22.769 --> 16:31.122
was clearly a rubber stamp situation, even when I 
first got on the board in 77. And the residents just

16:31.142 --> 16:38.032
resented that, and I personally think for good 
reason. Also, some of the tensions were

16:38.052 --> 16:41.177
heightened by the fact that The residents only had 
one representative on board. The board at that

16:45.807 --> 16:48.369
time, I think, was seven. And it has grown. It was 
eight. Yeah, I think seven developer appointed

16:51.953 --> 16:57.680
and one resident elected. So the development 
corporation, over time,

16:58.020 --> 17:10.033
began to see that it needed to change its style. And 
in response to requests from the community, which

17:10.925 --> 17:28.467
were militant requests, added resident elected 
people to the board even before the covenants

17:10.925 --> 17:28.467
required them to be added. And in some case, we gave 
up our seats. to enable that to happen in fact today

17:33.318 --> 17:59.089
one of our seats is held by a resident elected 
director we should have eight seats we only have

17:33.318 --> 17:59.089
seven because we gave up one seat

17:33.318 --> 17:59.089
so those are some of the tensions in the early years 
and when i took over the presidency of the board

17:33.318 --> 17:59.089
which i've had for 10 years my objectives were to 
eliminate those tensions and establish a

18:00.335 --> 18:04.961
partnership. I changed the mode of operating the 
board and I have encouraged even our own appointed

18:04.981 --> 18:24.148
people with the responsibility of the trust that 
has been given to them for proper management of the

18:04.981 --> 18:24.148
association. to speak out as the professionals 
that they are. And if they don't agree with

18:27.823 --> 18:31.094
something, I want to hear that. And we've made it a 
much stronger association as a result a couple of

18:31.736 --> 18:36.332
years ago. We were named the best managed large 
scale association in the Houston area and hope to

18:36.650 --> 18:46.261
win that award this year at the national level. 
They've just established a competition that I

18:46.281 --> 18:53.510
think will certainly come in the top two or three if 
not winning. And that's because I like to use the

18:54.331 --> 19:01.079
talents I have available to me and foolish not to. 
Other tensions tend to crop up. between the

19:04.342 --> 19:07.511
community and the Women's Corporation on 
specific issues.

19:10.920 --> 19:16.174
Most of them have to do

19:10.920 --> 19:16.174
with, well, I shouldn't say I mean, there have been 
