19:32.721 --> 19:40.028
a driveway directly onto Grosvenor Road, which 
would have been taking trees down and having them

19:32.721 --> 19:40.028
cleaned up. And the community virtually chained 
themselves in front of the bulldozers. And they

19:43.471 --> 19:46.313
could go quite to that, but it was close to that. And 
so we asked Exxon if they would change their plan,

19:47.086 --> 19:51.732
and they said okay. Exxon didn't want to do it 
because it would cost them money, but they agreed

19:52.273 --> 19:57.460
because of the opposition. And last I heard, that 
was the largest bro-sink gas station in the

19:58.401 --> 20:08.495
Houston area without a direct curb cutout to 
Grover's Mill. They've objected to signs,

20:09.076 --> 20:15.625
certain types of signs that were proposed to be put 
in. These are things that usually get resolved

20:16.600 --> 20:19.944
amicably. But those are good kind of objections, 
