when we built and filled Lake Woodlands. The

20:36.024 --> 20:40.570
community felt that they were not going to have 
enough access to the lake, and that became a big

20:36.024 --> 20:40.570
issue. So we adjusted our plans to get more points 
of access to the lake. Again, a feeling of this is

20:46.537 --> 20:54.190
our community, and we want to be part of it. We don't 
want to. And, you know, some of this is good. Last

20:58.919 --> 21:09.557
year, or earlier this year, just outside of the 
developed areas, some of the people who owned the

20:58.919 --> 21:09.557
mineral rights kind of drilled a gas well. We try to 
buy up all the mineral rights, mainly to prevent

21:10.718 --> 21:21.637
wells from being driven nearby or even in 
developed areas. Had we controlled all the

21:21.797 --> 21:26.045
mineral rights, that well never would have been 
built. But we didn't, so under state law you have to

21:26.065 --> 21:28.930
allow them. To drill it, we put in conditions in the 
contract. Thus, we controlled

21:36.073 --> 21:48.023
enough of the mineral rights and the surface 
rights to use quiet generators and things like

21:36.073 --> 21:48.023
that. But the community was just upset that there 
would be an oil well or a gas well, as it turned out,

21:48.043 --> 21:56.430
being drilled within eye contact of existing 
homes. And it had gotten noisy at times. Yeah,

21:58.897 --> 22:07.310
we caught the flak very directly. But that's 
something that we could not stop, although we

22:07.611 --> 22:14.802
tried to dissuade people from doing it. So it tends 
to be single-issue, single-issue oriented, and

22:14.822 --> 22:24.617
those issues come and go, and we almost always...

