and Women's Community Association takes over, 
will that sort of diminish some of your problems,

22:26.048 --> 22:34.619
maybe, or create new ones? Do you see any different 
direction that that group may pursue in terms of

22:35.420 --> 22:40.868
what their goals are? Well, I see a board

22:42.009 --> 22:51.742
that will have, when it starts out, ten elected and 
one appointed person. We still have one residual

22:51.762 --> 22:54.165
person on the board. Because it's predominantly 
elected and controlled by those people becoming

22:54.854 --> 23:14.965
very political, I think it will become political 
internal to the board, but I think it will also

22:54.854 --> 23:14.965
become much more political within the community 
